<treatmentCitationGroup id="A3FE8441FFBCFFC1FF41FA0BB696FA3F" box="[174,649,1435,1459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
<treatmentCitation id="024F857EFFBCFFC1FF41FA0BB620FA3F" author="Blackwall, J." box="[174,575,1437,1459]" page="99" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" year="1865">
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FF41FA0BB620FA3F" authority="Blackwall, 1865: 99" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityPageNumber="99" authorityYear="1865" box="[174,575,1437,1459]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tetragnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FF41FA0BB59DFA3E" box="[174,386,1437,1458]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Tetragnatha maculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBCFFC1FE67FA0BB620FA3F" author="Blackwall, J." box="[392,575,1437,1459]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref4323" refString="Blackwall, J. 1865. Descriptions of recently discovered spiders collected in the Cape de Verde Islands by John Gray, Esq. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (3), 80 - 101." type="journal article" year="1865">Blackwall, 1865: 99</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
(♂, 
<specimenCount id="95E868E6FFBCFFC1FD83FA0DB664FA3E" box="[620,635,1435,1458]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8351A36FFFBCFFC1FF0CFA42B069F923" blockId="5.[174,1233,1492,1711]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Note. This species was described based on specimens from St. Nicholas Island (
<collectingCountry id="FBF9E3FFFFBCFFC1FB7DFA42B4E9F983" name="Cape Verde" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands). The 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBCFFC1FE73FA62B631F983" author="WSC" box="[412,558,1524,1551]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" refId="ref5187" refString="WSC, 2017. World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. (http: // wsc. nmbe. ch, version 18.0; accessed: 28.02.2017)." type="url" year="2017">WSC (2017)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously indicates that the species is known from the female only, although 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBCFFC1FE59F982B664F9A3" author="Blackwall, J." box="[438,635,1556,1583]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref4323" refString="Blackwall, J. 1865. Descriptions of recently discovered spiders collected in the Cape de Verde Islands by John Gray, Esq. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (3), 80 - 101." type="journal article" year="1865">Blackwall (1865)</bibRefCitation>
described the male palp and clearly indicated that he had both male and female. 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBCFFC1FDF5F9A2B6A3F9C3" author="Simon, E." box="[538,700,1588,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" pagination="259 - 314" refId="ref5076" refString="Simon, E. 1883. Etudes arachnologiques. 14 e Memoire. XXI. Materiaux pour servir a la faune arachnologique des iles de l'Ocean Atlantique (Acores, Madere, Salvages, Canaries, Cap Vert, Sainte-Helene et Bermudes). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 3 (6), 259 - 314." type="journal article" year="1883">Simon (1883)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned this species as 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FC12F9A3B0B0F9C2" baseAuthorityName="Blackwall" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1021,1199,1588,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FC12F9A3B0B0F9C2" box="[1021,1199,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Meta maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a list of species from 
<collectingCountry id="FBF9E3FFFFBCFFC1FE47F9C2B62BF9E3" box="[424,564,1620,1647]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands, and provided no reason why he transferred this species to 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FECCF9E3B57FF902" baseAuthorityName="WSC" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[291,352,1653,1678]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FECCF9E3B57FF902" box="[291,352,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Meta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, the size of the species, 1/5 of an inch (about 
<quantity id="44160E8AFFBCFFC1FC1CF9E2B024F903" box="[1011,1083,1652,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
), is too small for 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FF38F903B50BF922" baseAuthorityName="WSC" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[215,276,1685,1710]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FF38F903B50BF922" box="[215,276,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Meta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FEA1F902B5A2F922" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1941" box="[334,445,1684,1710]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FEA1F902B5A2F922" box="[334,445,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Metellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we are placing this species back in 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBCFFC1FC31F902B071F922" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[990,1134,1684,1710]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Tetragnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBCFFC1FC31F902B071F922" box="[990,1134,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Tetragnatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
